TM17-157/158 — Staff PDF Export Display Options for Reporting

Overview

This update adds staff-facing PDF export configuration to the reporting page so authorized users can control how report content is presented when exporting to PDF.

Previously, the reporting page allowed downloads in multiple formats, but PDF export did not provide configurable presentation options for how report visuals and numeric data should be included. This update introduces staff-only controls that let users choose whether the PDF contains charts only, data table only, or both, and whether chart/table content should appear side-by-side or sequentially. It also restructures PDF output into a cleaner print-ready layout so exported reports better align with presentation guidelines.

---------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Frontend Integration — Staff PDF Export Controls
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Affected component: Reporting page (`ReportingPage`)

Changes made:

- Added staff-only PDF export settings to the existing download toolbar
- Introduced a content selection control for:
  - Charts only
  - Data table only
  - Both
- Introduced a layout selection control for:
  - Side-by-side
  - Sequential
- Limited these controls to staff/admin users so public users do not see PDF presentation settings
- Kept the rest of the reporting workflow unchanged, including existing export buttons and shareable link behavior

Behavior breakdown:

| Condition | Result |
|-----------|--------|
| User is public | PDF configuration controls are not shown |
| User is staff/admin | PDF content and layout options are available |
| PDF content = Charts only | Export includes graphical presentation only |
| PDF content = Data table only | Export includes numeric/tabular presentation only |
| PDF content = Both | Export includes both graphical and numeric content |
| Layout = Side-by-side | Charts and table render in a two-column PDF layout |
| Layout = Sequential | Charts and table render one after another vertically |

