2. PDF Export Logic — Configurable Presentation Output
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Affected logic: `handleDownload('pdf')` and PDF generation helpers

Changes made:

- Added new state values to track PDF export preferences:
  - `pdfDisplayMode`
  - `pdfLayoutMode`
- Updated PDF generation so export output is built dynamically from the selected options
- Created a print-ready HTML template for PDF output instead of dumping raw report data
- Added a structured PDF header with report metadata such as:
  - initiative name
  - generated date
  - selected display mode
  - selected layout mode
- Preserved summary and explainability content in the PDF when available
- Ensured PDF generation continues to work through the existing browser print flow with minimal disruption to the current implementation

Behavior breakdown:

| Selection | PDF Result |
|-----------|------------|
| Charts only | Only chart sections are rendered |
| Data table only | Only table content is rendered |
| Both + Side-by-side | Chart and table cards render next to each other |
| Both + Sequential | Chart and table cards stack vertically |
| No chart data available | PDF shows a fallback “No chart data available” state |
| No table data available | PDF shows a fallback “No table data available” state |

