3. Graphical and Numeric Presentation Support
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Affected areas: chart formatting and table formatting inside PDF export

Changes made:

- Added chart-section extraction logic based on normalized report data
- Reused available `chartData` and `trendData` to support graphical output in export mode
- Built simple print-safe bar visualizations for charts so graphical information is still represented in PDF without relying on interactive UI components
- Added table rendering logic using normalized `tableData`
- Automatically derived table columns from the available dataset
- Preserved both visual and numeric reporting paths so staff can choose the presentation style required for the audience

Behavior breakdown:

| Data Type | Presentation Mode |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `chartData` / `trendData` | Graphical bar-based PDF presentation |
| `tableData` | Numeric tabular PDF presentation |
| Both available | Export supports combined visual + numeric reporting |
| Partial data available | PDF gracefully renders whichever sections exist |

