4. Presentation Guideline Conformance — Print-Friendly PDF Layout
---------------------------------------------------------------------

Affected area: PDF HTML/CSS template

Changes made:

- Replaced the basic export output with a styled print document
- Added clear visual hierarchy for:
  - page title
  - metadata
  - summary
  - explainability
  - charts
  - data table
- Applied print-friendly spacing, borders, and typography
- Added card-based grouping to make the PDF easier to review and present
- Prevented layout clutter by using:
  - controlled section spacing
  - bounded chart widths
  - table wrapping
  - print-safe page margins
- Used side-by-side layout only when both content types are selected, otherwise defaulting naturally to a single-section flow

Behavior breakdown:

| Requirement | Implementation |
|-------------|----------------|
| Charts only / table only / both | Supported via `pdfDisplayMode` |
| Side-by-side / sequential layout | Supported via `pdfLayoutMode` |
| Graphical and numeric presentation | Supported through chart and table rendering |
| Conform to presentation guidelines | Achieved with structured print styling and section hierarchy |

