User Experience Improvements
---------------------------------------------------------------------

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| PDF export had no presentation options | Staff can control PDF content and layout before export |
| PDF output was not tailored for charts vs. tables | Users can export charts only, table only, or both |
| No configurable layout for combined content | Users can choose side-by-side or sequential presentation |
| Exported PDF was less presentation-ready | PDF now uses a cleaner structured report layout |
| Graphical and numeric data were not clearly separated in export behavior | Both content types are now intentionally supported and selectable |

This update adds staff-configurable PDF export presentation options to the reporting page, supports both graphical and numeric report output, and improves the final PDF layout so exports are more useful for formal sharing and presentation without introducing unnecessary changes to the existing reporting workflow.